==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synclastic
<hw>Syn*clas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>syn-</ets> + Gr. <grk>kla^n</grk> to break.]</ety> <fld>(Math.
Physics)</fld> <def>Curved toward the same side in all directions; --
said of surfaces which in all directions around any point bend away from
a tangent plane toward the same side, as the surface of a sphere; --
opposed to anticlastic.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synclinal</ent>⟦br⟧
